         <div xml:id="main">
            <head type="incipit">
               <supplied reason="XTF-compatibility">3/5/85 ¶  ¶ Herewith the duplicate of the bill of lading, dear Sir Joseph, concerning the two growing stems of Xanthorrhoea australis sent. ¶  ¶ As regards the system. position of Fropiera, I still th...</supplied>
            </head>
            <p rend="number" xml:lang="en">85.05.03</p>
            <p rend="correspondent" xml:lang="en">To Joseph Hooker</p>
            <p rend="location" xml:lang="en">RBG Kew, Kew correspondence, Australia, Mueller, 1882-90, f. 145.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="en">3/5/85</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Herewith the duplicate of the bill of lading, dear Sir Joseph, concerning the two growing stems of <name key="Xanthorrhoea">Xanthorrhoea</name> australis sent.<note xml:id="ftn1" type="footnote" n="1">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3346in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3346in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>See M to J. Hooker, 24 May 1885.</p>
               </note>
            </p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>As regards the system. position of <name key="Fropiera">Fropiera</name>, I still think that it belongs to the Cohors of <name key="Guttiferae">Guttiferae</name>, if not to that order.<note xml:id="ftn2" type="footnote" n="2">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3346in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3346in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>See M to J. Hooker<seg style="color: #000000; ">, 27 January</seg> 1885.</p>
               </note> Dotted leaves, as you are well aware, occur also in <name key="Mammea">Mammea</name>; the sessile stigma points also to <name key="Guttiferae">Guttiferae</name>; while the seeds are tessellated and minute as in <name key="Hypericum">Hypericum</name> &amp; <name key="Elatine">Elatine</name>. I had some idea, to write a few notes on this genus, but rather leave the consideration of the matter to yourself. This might be a good opportunity for your nobile<note xml:id="ftn3" type="footnote" n="3">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3346in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3346in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     <seg style="">
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>i.e. noble.</seg>
                  </p>
               </note> Laboratory cooperators to investigate, whether any <seg style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">diagnostic</hi>
               </seg>
               <seg style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">differences</hi>
               </seg> between the oilglands of Myrtaceae and <name key="Hypericinae">Hypericinae</name> could be found out, which likely exist. The dots of <name key="Hypericum">Hypericum</name> are rather resin- than oil-dots so that in this respect <name key="Fropiera">Fropiera</name> would require examination chemically and optically.</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
               xml:lang="en">With best regards</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Ferd. von Mueller.</p>
